{"name": "vdk-ingest-http", "metadata": {"name": "vdk-ingest-http", "version": "0.2.1431637373", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/vmware/versatile-data-kit", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["vdk-core", "simplejson"], "summary": "Versatile Data Kit SDK ingestion plugin to ingest data via http requests.", "upload_time": 1724915952}, "documentation": ["### VDK-INGEST-HTTP Plugin\n\n<a href=\"https://pypistats.org/packages/vdk-ingest-http\" alt=\"Monthly Downloads\">\n        <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/vdk-ingest-http.svg\" alt=\"monthly download count for vdk-ingest-http\"></a>\n\nThis plugin provides functionality to ingest data over http.\n\n### Usage\n\nTo use the plugin, just install it, and set the `method` attribute of `send_object_for_ingestion()`,\nand `send_tabular_data_for_ingestion()` functions to _\"http\"_.\n\nExample:\n```python\ndef run(job_input: IJobInput):\n    # Do something to get data for ingestion\n    payload = get_some_data()\n\n    # Ingest the data\n    job_input.send_object_for_ingestion(payload=payload,\n                                        destination_table=\"aa_test_table\",\n                                        method=\"http\",\n                                        target=\"http://example.com/data-source\"\n                                        )\n```\nThe above example shows how to ingest json data. In this case, there are three arguments that are required: `payload`,\n`method` and `target`. This would be fixed in the future, so that only `payload` would be required.\n<br>\nThe payload needs to be a json object, and should contain the `destination_table` inside, using the `@table` key. For example:\n```\n{\n    \"@table\": \"destination_table_name\",\n    \"column1\": \"value1\",\n    \"column2\": \"value2\",\n    \"column3\": \"value3\",\n}\n```\nThe `method` attribute needs to be provided for the time being.\n<br>\nThe `target` attribute should specify the url endpoint, where the data will be ingested.\n\n### Testing\n\nTo develop or test locally (from the current directory)\n```bash\n# install dev and test dependencies\npip install -r requirements\n# install the plugin in editable mode\npip install -e .\n# run the tests\npytest\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "vdk.plugin.ingest_http.ingest_http_plugin", "documentation": ["VDK-ingest-file plugin script.", "Copyright 2023-2024 Broadcom", "SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0"], "functions": [{"name": "vdk.plugin.ingest_http.ingest_http_plugin.vdk_configure", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "config_builder", "type": {"name": "ConfigurationBuilder", "xref": {"fqname": "vdk.internal.core.config.ConfigurationBuilder", "project": "vdk-core"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Here we define what configuration settings are needed for the Ingest HTTP plugin with reasonable defaults"]}, {"name": "vdk.plugin.ingest_http.ingest_http_plugin.initialize_job", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "context", "type": {"name": "JobContext", "xref": {"fqname": "vdk.internal.builtin_plugins.run.job_context.JobContext", "project": "vdk-core"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "vdk.plugin.ingest_http.ingest_http_plugin.log", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "vdk.plugin.ingest_http.ingest_over_http", "documentation": ["Copyright 2023-2024 Broadcom", "SPDX-License-Identifier: A